# Bragg Family Website (braggfam.com)

This is a small static family website — currently a single-page "Bragg Family
Adventure Guide". There is no framework, no build step, and no package manager.

## Hosting

- Hosted on **GitHub Pages** from the `main` branch (root `/`) of the public
  repo `Tomicle/braggfam` (remote `origin`).
- Custom domain: **braggfam.com**, configured via the `CNAME` file in the repo
  root. **Never delete or edit `CNAME`** — the custom domain breaks without it.
- HTTPS is handled automatically by GitHub Pages (Let's Encrypt).
- DNS lives at Namecheap: four A records on `@` pointing to GitHub Pages IPs
  and a `www` CNAME to `tomicle.github.io`. Don't suggest DNS changes unless
  something is broken.

## File map

- `index.html` — the entire live site (markup + all CSS in an inline `<style>` block)
- `CNAME` — custom domain config for GitHub Pages (contents: `braggfam.com`)
- `Bragg Family Adventure Guide.html` — original browser-saved source the site
  came from. Local reference only; do NOT commit it and do NOT edit it.
- `CLOUDFLARE-MIGRATION-PLAN.md` — future migration notes. Local only; do NOT
  commit it (it may eventually contain family email addresses).
- `README.md` — human-facing guide to this setup.

## Publishing changes live

Edit `index.html`, then commit and push to `main`:

```bash
git add index.html && git commit -m "Describe the change" && git push
```

GitHub Pages redeploys automatically; changes are live at https://braggfam.com
in about a minute. There is nothing else to run.

## Privacy rule (important)

The repo is **public**. Never commit personal details: home addresses, phone
numbers, email addresses, travel dates tied to an empty house, etc. If the
family wants private content, that's what the Cloudflare migration plan is for.
